synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involved pulverizing and mixing Li2S, GeS2, P2S5, and Sb2S5 powders in varying ratios, ball milling the mixture, tableting it into a disc at 100 MPa, sintering it in a vacuum quartz tube at a controlled temperature program reaching 550°C over 4 hours, holding for 4 hours, then cooling to 50°C over 4 hours to produce Li10Ge(P1-aSba)2S12 solid electrolyte material with adjustable parameter a.
